The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 October is 88,743 (10,228.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 October, there were 4,229 new confirmed cases (487.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 October, there were 3,085 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 37% (1,144 extra cases).
